Majalisar Dinkin Duniya ta ce dubban masu adawa da Pakistan a Afghanistan
ISLAMABAD - Wani rahoton Majalisar Dinkin Duniya ya ce sama da ‘yan tawayen Pakistan 6,000 ke buya a Afghanistan, mafi yawansu na haramtacciyar kungiyar Taliban ce ta Pakistan da ke da alhakin kai hari kan sojojin Pakistan da kuma fararen hula.
Rahoton da aka fitar a wannan makon ya ce kungiyar, wacce aka fi sani da Tehreek-e-Taliban (TTP), ta hade da wani reshen Afghanistan da ke kungiyar IS.
Wasu daga cikin membobin TTP har sun shiga kungiyar ta IS, wacce ke da hedikwata a gabashin Afghanistan.
Gwamnatin Afghanistan ba ta ba da amsa ba a ranar Lahadi ga buƙatun da Kamfanin Dillancin Labarai na Associated Press ya yi don yin sharhi.
Rahoton ya ce IS a Afghanistan, da aka fi sani da IS a lardin Khorasan, ya sha da kyar daga jami’an tsaron Afghanistan da na Amurka da na NATO, har ma a wasu lokutan kungiyar Taliban ta Afghanistan.
Rahoton ya fito ne daga kungiyar bincike da sanya takunkumi ta Majalisar Dinkin Duniya, wacce ke bin diddigin kungiyoyin 'yan ta'adda a duniya.
Rahoton ya kiyasta mambobin kungiyar ta IS a Afghanistan da 2,200, kuma yayin da shugabancin ta ya kare, har yanzu kungiyar ta IS tana cikin shugabannin ta wani dan kasar Syria Abu Said Mohammad al-Khorasani.
